WEBVTT

00:00:10.012 --> 00:00:12.224
Finding and recruiting employees is

00:00:12.224 --> 00:00:14.343
a key step in helping an organization

00:00:14.339 --> 00:00:16.594
achieve its goals.

00:00:16.577 --> 00:00:19.046
As a sub-delegated manager, you will be

00:00:19.018 --> 00:00:21.204
asked to staff positions within your

00:00:21.189 --> 00:00:23.631
section or work unit by finding the skills

00:00:23.623 --> 00:00:26.914
and other attributes needed for the work.

00:00:28.899 --> 00:00:30.884
Federal public service managers and

00:00:30.859 --> 00:00:33.613
human resources professionals must comply

00:00:33.609 --> 00:00:36.132
with a variety of policies and legislation

00:00:36.122 --> 00:00:39.415
governing how staffing processes are conducted.

00:00:39.408 --> 00:00:43.222
These laws, regulations and policies support and

00:00:43.207 --> 00:00:46.307
promote impartial appointments, based on merit,

00:00:46.295 --> 00:00:48.642
which help advance diversity and

00:00:48.630 --> 00:00:51.636
inclusion in the workplace.

00:00:52.750 --> 00:00:55.511
In this section you will learn to

00:00:55.493 --> 00:00:58.292
identify your staffing needs,

00:00:58.268 --> 00:01:01.213
recall your staffing obligations, and

00:01:01.185 --> 00:01:04.569
recognize considerations for staffing a position.

00:01:05.566 --> 00:01:06.890
This section should take you

00:01:06.882 --> 00:01:11.045
approximately 20 minutes to complete.

00:01:19.811 --> 00:01:21.683
In determining your staffing needs,

00:01:21.663 --> 00:01:24.173
consider various sources of information.

00:01:24.166 --> 00:01:26.693
A few good sources to begin with are your

00:01:26.683 --> 00:01:29.350
business objectives, your organizational goals

00:01:29.338 --> 00:01:32.381
and the public service workforce goals.

00:01:32.375 --> 00:01:34.530
Considering your business objectives when

00:01:34.509 --> 00:01:36.994
staffing will help ensure that your programs

00:01:36.973 --> 00:01:40.334
and services are properly managed and delivered.

00:01:40.315 --> 00:01:42.868
For clarity on business objectives,

00:01:42.844 --> 00:01:45.269
consult documents such as business plans,

00:01:45.248 --> 00:01:47.498
performance agreements, Treasury Board

00:01:47.481 --> 00:01:50.369
submissions, and Cabinet documents.

00:01:50.364 --> 00:01:52.527
When considering your business objectives,

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:54.753
ask yourself the following questions.

00:01:54.733 --> 00:01:56.741
Do my objectives align with

00:01:56.734 --> 00:01:58.438
the higher-level priorities? 

00:01:58.428 --> 00:02:01.543
And, what qualifications will contribute

00:02:01.530 --> 00:02:04.179
to meeting the business requirements?

00:02:04.162 --> 00:02:06.615
Business objectives are guided by organizational 

00:02:06.617 --> 00:02:09.065
and public service workforce goals. 

00:02:09.039 --> 00:02:10.485
Those goals are set

00:02:10.473 --> 00:02:12.320
by the Clerk of the Privy Council,

00:02:12.310 --> 00:02:17.016
the Treasury Board, deputy heads and management.

00:02:17.015 --> 00:02:20.223
Here are some examples of priorities at this level:

00:02:20.222 --> 00:02:21.627
building a diverse, equitable

00:02:21.622 --> 00:02:24.472
and inclusive public service; correcting

00:02:24.466 --> 00:02:26.962
conditions of disadvantage in employment;

00:02:26.972 --> 00:02:29.382
placing employees who are affected

00:02:29.379 --> 00:02:31.492
by workforce adjustment;

00:02:31.450 --> 00:02:33.682
and building organizational capacity

00:02:33.673 --> 00:02:36.302
and developing competencies.

00:02:36.295 --> 00:02:37.991
Organizational and public service

00:02:37.992 --> 00:02:40.737
workforce goals are framed by

00:02:40.719 --> 00:02:42.707
legislation including the Public Service

00:02:42.669 --> 00:02:44.764
Employment Act,

00:02:44.748 --> 00:02:46.064
Accessible Canada Act,

00:02:46.054 --> 00:02:47.727
Employment Equity Act,

00:02:47.710 --> 00:02:50.006
Canadian Human Rights Act,

00:02:50.006 --> 00:02:51.630
Official Languages Act,

00:02:51.615 --> 00:02:55.056
and the Constitution of Canada;

00:02:55.039 --> 00:02:57.020
agreements like the Nunavut Land Claims

00:02:57.013 --> 00:02:58.870
Agreement and even the Canadian

00:02:58.866 --> 00:03:01.743
Free Trade Agreement, as well as

00:03:01.727 --> 00:03:04.153
your Minister's mandate, statements by

00:03:04.138 --> 00:03:05.814
the Clerk of the Privy Council,

00:03:05.818 --> 00:03:09.522
and the Speech from the Throne.

00:03:21.444 --> 00:03:23.562
Before you initiate an appointment process,

00:03:23.547 --> 00:03:26.302
it’s important to be acquainted with the legislation,

00:03:26.276 --> 00:03:29.680
policies and guidelines that govern appointments.

00:03:29.657 --> 00:03:31.591
These include the Public Service Commission’s

00:03:31.586 --> 00:03:33.820
Appointment Framework and the Treasury Board’s

00:03:33.804 --> 00:03:35.586
policy framework, as well as your

00:03:35.570 --> 00:03:38.663
organizational staffing framework.

00:03:38.650 --> 00:03:40.543
The purpose of the Employment Equity Act

00:03:40.522 --> 00:03:42.562
is to achieve equality in the workplace

00:03:42.550 --> 00:03:44.437
and to correct conditions of disadvantage

00:03:44.425 --> 00:03:47.069
in employment for such designated groups as:

00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:49.856
women, Aboriginal peoples,

00:03:49.850 --> 00:03:51.258
persons with disabilities and

00:03:51.238 --> 00:03:53.865
members of visible minorities.

00:03:53.838 --> 00:03:56.393
The Act requires that every employer identify

00:03:56.395 --> 00:03:58.751
and eliminate employment barriers against

00:03:58.737 --> 00:04:01.484
persons in the identified groups.

00:04:01.485 --> 00:04:04.230
Employers must also institute positive policies and

00:04:04.220 --> 00:04:06.560
practices and make reasonable accommodations

00:04:06.549 --> 00:04:08.853
to ensure their workforce reflects

00:04:08.838 --> 00:04:11.241
the diversity of Canadians.

00:04:12.942 --> 00:04:15.401
The Accessible Canada Act is intended to promote

00:04:15.383 --> 00:04:17.663
the full and equal participation of all persons,

00:04:17.651 --> 00:04:21.295
especially persons with disabilities, in society.

00:04:21.290 --> 00:04:23.875
This act strives to proactively eliminate and

00:04:23.862 --> 00:04:26.092
prevent barriers in seven areas under

00:04:26.057 --> 00:04:28.346
federal jurisdiction, including employment,

00:04:28.317 --> 00:04:30.956
in order to ensure greater opportunities

00:04:30.951 --> 00:04:33.908
for persons with disabilities.

00:04:33.889 --> 00:04:35.278
The Public Service Commission’s

00:04:35.281 --> 00:04:37.572
Appointment Framework guides deputy heads

00:04:37.569 --> 00:04:39.583
in building their own staffing systems

00:04:39.564 --> 00:04:41.965
adapted to their needs and in ensuring that

00:04:41.953 --> 00:04:43.278
they comply with legislative

00:04:43.257 --> 00:04:44.998
and policy requirements. 

00:04:44.978 --> 00:04:47.068
It is made up of

00:04:47.067 --> 00:04:49.399
1) the Public Service Employment Act

00:04:49.387 --> 00:04:51.769
and any applicable exclusion approval orders

00:04:51.763 --> 00:04:54.470
and regulations. The full list of List of Acts,

00:04:54.442 --> 00:04:58.516
Regulations and Orders can be found online.

00:04:58.490 --> 00:05:00.264
2) The Public Service Commission’s 

00:05:00.254 --> 00:05:02.464
Appointment Policy.

00:05:02.453 --> 00:05:04.247
3) Appointment Delegation

00:05:04.231 --> 00:05:08.416
and Accountability Instrument.

00:05:10.062 --> 00:05:11.591
Components of the Treasury Board’s

00:05:11.572 --> 00:05:13.817
policy framework also have a role to play

00:05:13.824 --> 00:05:15.170
in the staffing process. 

00:05:15.175 --> 00:05:17.080
It refers to the following documents 

00:05:17.074 --> 00:05:20.122
(links available in the toolkit).

00:05:20.120 --> 00:05:23.055
1) The Values and Ethics Code for the Public Sector,

00:05:23.063 --> 00:05:25.823
which guides managers in their staffing thinking

00:05:25.814 --> 00:05:27.733
and decision making.

00:05:27.731 --> 00:05:30.454
2) The Financial Administration Act, in particular

00:05:30.447 --> 00:05:33.610
the Human Resources Management section.

00:05:33.598 --> 00:05:35.901
3) The Policy on People Management and

00:05:35.882 --> 00:05:38.591
directives which cover deployments, assignments,

00:05:38.586 --> 00:05:41.471
secondments, reclassifications, official languages

00:05:41.466 --> 00:05:44.665
in relation to staffing, and the duty to accommodate

00:05:44.658 --> 00:05:46.879
which outlines how to make staffing processes

00:05:46.853 --> 00:05:50.384
as inclusive and accessible as possible.

00:05:50.377 --> 00:05:53.488
4) Programs such as: employment equity,

00:05:53.487 --> 00:05:56.299
diversity and inclusion, student programs,

00:05:56.287 --> 00:05:58.796
and the Interchange Canada program.

00:05:58.794 --> 00:06:02.167
5) Qualification standards in relation to education,

00:06:02.152 --> 00:06:04.967
occupational certification, official languages

00:06:04.961 --> 00:06:07.824
and other requirements to qualify for employment

00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:11.286
in the core public service.

