00:06:44.016 --> 00:06:47.110
As a sub-delegated manager, you are responsible for

00:06:47.105 --> 00:06:50.490
making decisions that are subdelegated to you and

00:06:50.464 --> 00:06:53.138
for working in partnership with HR.

00:06:53.117 --> 00:06:55.241
There are three lenses to apply

00:06:55.239 --> 00:06:58.371
when staffing a position: 

00:06:58.366 --> 00:07:01.231
diversity, equity and inclusion;

00:07:01.214 --> 00:07:03.654
business objectives and the judicious management

00:07:03.654 --> 00:07:07.774
of resources; and integrity and ethics.

00:07:07.759 --> 00:07:10.494
In order to conduct a fair and inclusive process

00:07:10.468 --> 00:07:12.794
and to hire qualified individuals to form

00:07:12.776 --> 00:07:14.945
a diverse workforce that reflects the Canadian

00:07:14.937 --> 00:07:17.959
population and meets your organizational needs,

00:07:17.937 --> 00:07:21.285
the following must be done.

00:07:22.737 --> 00:07:25.038
Take into account employment equity objectives <br>

00:07:25.007 --> 00:07:28.257
and adopt inclusive practices.

00:07:28.237 --> 00:07:30.538
Ensure that hiring processes are conducted

00:07:30.528 --> 00:07:33.840
in good faith, are free from bias and

00:07:33.836 --> 00:07:36.230
are impartial in a manner that is supportive

00:07:36.225 --> 00:07:40.519
of an individual’s right to accommodation.

00:07:40.506 --> 00:07:42.640
Establish effective merit criteria that reflect

00:07:42.608 --> 00:07:45.969
the requirements of the position or work unit

00:07:45.945 --> 00:07:48.559
and consider the organization's business needs.

00:07:48.546 --> 00:07:52.775
For example, equity-seeking groups.

00:07:52.768 --> 00:07:54.377
Select a process type 

00:07:54.353 --> 00:07:55.957
(appointment or administrative, 

00:07:55.946 --> 00:07:57.757
advertised or non-advertised,

00:07:57.747 --> 00:08:00.024
internal or external).

00:08:00.017 --> 00:08:02.596
Determine who will be eligible to apply

00:08:02.586 --> 00:08:06.087
by establishing the area of selection or recourse.

00:08:06.063 --> 00:08:09.363
Identify and seek to reduce unconscious biases

00:08:09.343 --> 00:08:13.153
(recruitment, assessment, selection).

00:08:13.153 --> 00:08:14.817
Conduct an objective assessment of

00:08:14.782 --> 00:08:17.907
each candidate’s qualifications and

00:08:17.915 --> 00:08:20.038
assess the candidate in their official language of

00:08:20.003 --> 00:08:21.938
choice without regard to the location of the

00:08:21.934 --> 00:08:25.004
official languages requirements of the position;

00:08:24.986 --> 00:08:27.286
provide accommodations by being proactive

00:08:27.276 --> 00:08:29.161
and responsive to requests;

00:08:29.138 --> 00:08:31.202
gather enough information from each candidate

00:08:31.177 --> 00:08:32.800
to make a fair decision;

00:08:32.787 --> 00:08:35.191
use a variety of complementary sources and

00:08:35.176 --> 00:08:37.151
assessment tools to increase the validity

00:08:37.137 --> 00:08:39.580
and reliability of the assessment;

00:08:39.557 --> 00:08:41.539
apply to each candidate the same standard

00:08:41.528 --> 00:08:44.509
for a qualification, that is the same definition

00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:47.101
or indicators) established for the process;

00:08:47.090 --> 00:08:48.873
ensure the quality of the assessment

00:08:48.860 --> 00:08:51.033
by consulting with experts and stakeholders

00:08:51.009 --> 00:08:53.013
on the selection process and the development

00:08:53.009 --> 00:08:55.308
of tools and their use in the assessment

00:08:55.298 --> 00:08:57.363
of candidates.

00:09:01.850 --> 00:09:03.972
Ensure appointments are based on merit

00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:06.732
and respect the order of precedence.

00:09:06.708 --> 00:09:09.812
Consider priority entitlement provisions,

00:09:09.799 --> 00:09:12.773
preference for veterans, Canadian citizens,

00:09:12.750 --> 00:09:15.182
permanent residents, and obligations set out

00:09:15.179 --> 00:09:17.212
in claim agreements such as the Nunavut

00:09:17.192 --> 00:09:18.665
Land Claims Agreement, and the

00:09:18.645 --> 00:09:20.665
Canadian Free Trade Agreement.

00:09:20.635 --> 00:09:22.545
For more details, please consult

00:09:22.538 --> 00:09:24.632
the Appointment Delegation and Accountability

00:09:24.620 --> 00:09:29.268
Instrument and the Appointment Policy.

00:09:30.467 --> 00:09:32.768
To conduct an effective process that achieves

00:09:32.749 --> 00:09:34.483
business objectives through the judicious

00:09:34.479 --> 00:09:36.778
management of resources, consider:

00:09:36.758 --> 00:09:38.201
keeping your staffing objectives

00:09:38.196 --> 00:09:40.123
in mind throughout the process;

00:09:40.127 --> 00:09:42.801
planning and preparing the staffing process

00:09:42.788 --> 00:09:44.538
prior to launching it;

00:09:44.529 --> 00:09:46.578
using flexibilities provided in the

00:09:46.567 --> 00:09:48.418
Public Service Employment Act and

00:09:48.408 --> 00:09:50.406
make reasonable adaptations

00:09:50.399 --> 00:09:53.807
as the circumstances evolve; promoting

00:09:53.798 --> 00:09:56.097
engagement and retention by being transparent

00:09:56.106 --> 00:09:59.026
with applicants and employees.

00:10:00.026 --> 00:10:01.979
To conduct a process based on integrity

00:10:01.948 --> 00:10:05.011
and ethics these 5 steps are necessary.

00:10:04.977 --> 00:10:07.073
Comply with the requirements of the staffing

00:10:07.057 --> 00:10:09.651
framework (public service and departmental)

00:10:09.627 --> 00:10:12.686
and exercise flexibility by suggesting solutions

00:10:12.678 --> 00:10:14.978
and adaptations for the assessment tools

00:10:14.978 --> 00:10:18.083
and approach in order to ensure a fair assessment

00:10:18.076 --> 00:10:23.941
of each candidate’s qualifications.

00:10:23.926 --> 00:10:26.271
Use one of the flexibilities provided for

00:10:26.258 --> 00:10:28.629
in the Public Service Employment Act.

00:10:28.618 --> 00:10:31.561
For example: focus exclusively on members

00:10:31.528 --> 00:10:33.829
of designated employment equity groups

00:10:33.808 --> 00:10:35.989
or expand the area of selection

00:10:35.966 --> 00:10:39.041
that applies to these groups.

00:10:39.028 --> 00:10:41.081
Establish an organizational need to

00:10:41.048 --> 00:10:42.605
select individuals who have declared

00:10:42.606 --> 00:10:44.442
that they belong to a designated group

00:10:44.438 --> 00:10:47.065
that is currently or is expected to be

00:10:47.036 --> 00:10:49.005
under-represented. 

00:10:49.005 --> 00:10:51.145
In a non-advertised process,

00:10:51.118 --> 00:10:53.242
appoint a person belonging to one

00:10:53.208 --> 00:10:59.025
of the designated groups.

00:10:59.007 --> 00:11:01.003
Make reasonable decisions based on

00:11:00.996 --> 00:11:03.735
valid and reliable information related to

00:11:03.708 --> 00:11:08.436
each candidate and for each process.

00:11:08.428 --> 00:11:11.184
Focus on merit rather than on likeability

00:11:11.187 --> 00:11:13.919
or other sources of bias.

00:11:16.288 --> 00:11:18.920
Be able to clearly explain decisions and

00:11:18.908 --> 00:11:21.139
document appointment information including

00:11:21.126 --> 00:11:24.209
your decisions and considerations.

